<div class="gallery fadeGallery">
  <h2> Motherboards </h2>

  <br>
  
  <p>
    
    Motherboards are the most important part of your Personal Computer. The motherboard has a preinstalled program called the UEFI or BIOS which allows your hardware communicate with the software such as windows or linux. The motherboard is where you connect every component to. Each component will be connected to the motherboard in one way or another. </p>
    <br>
    <p>
    You must connect your sata cables to the hard drive and to the hard drive itself for the hard drive to be seen by the UEFI or BIOS. To use a graphics card you must connect it into the PCI-E slots on your motherboard add an external power connector if needed. One of the most important part of a motherboard, is its socket type, these range from LGA sockets to PGA sockets. The sockets are where you put your processor in, most Intel processors use LGA sockets and most AMD processors will use PGA sockets. Make sure your processor is compatible with the motherboard you are getting.

  </p>
</div>

